<br>
The dropping of those two atomic bombs should probably be considered two of the darkest days in man-kinds dark history.  However, horrible as the destruction and death was, I believe it is safe to assume that had the United States attempted to land troops and conquer all major islands in the chain, the destruction and death toll would have been much much greater not only for Japan, but also for the United States.<br>
